- \(P(S = 10) = (0.7)^{10} = 0.0282475249\)
- \(P(S = 9) = \binom{10}{9} (0.7)^9 (0.3) = 10 \times (0.7)^9 \times 0.3 = 0.121060821\)
- \(P(S > 8) = 0.0282475249 + 0.121060821 = 0.1493083459\)

The probability that a single drug has at most 8 successes is:
- \(P(S \leq 8) = 1 - P(S > 8) = 1 - 0.1493083459 = 0.8506916541\)

Since the drugs are independent, the probability that all three drugs have at most 8 successes is:
- \(P(\text{all} \leq 8) = (0.8506916541)^3 \approx 0.615624907\)

The probability that the maximum number of successes exceeds eight is the complement:
- \(P(\max > 8) = 1 - P(\text{all} \leq 8) = 1 - 0.615624907 = 0.384375093\)

