For the fourth white ball to be the fourth ball drawn, the first three draws must all be white (so exactly three white balls are drawn in the first three draws), and the fourth draw must also be white. Since each draw is independent with replacement, the probability is the probability of drawing white on all four draws.

The probability of drawing white on a single draw is \( 0.5 \), so:
