 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The problem requires finding the probability \(P(52.761 \leq \bar{X} \leq 54.453)\) for the sample mean \(\bar{X}\) of a random sample of size \(n = 47\) from a population with mean \(\mu = 54.030\) and standard deviation \(\sigma = 5.8\). By the Central Limit Theorem, since \(n = 47 > 30\), the sampling distribution of \(\bar{X}\) is approximately normal with mean \(\mu_{\bar{X}} = \mu = 54.030\) and standard deviation \(\sigma_{\bar{X}} = \frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{n}} = \frac{5.8}{\sqrt{47}}\).

