Solution: The probability that at least one student rolls a number matching their student number is calculated as the complement of the probability that no matches occur. With 12 students each rolling a fair 12-sided die, the probability that a specific student does not roll their own number is \( \frac{11}{12} \). Since the dice rolls are independent, the probability that no matches occur is \( \left( \frac{11}{12} \right)^{12} \).

